CHANGELOG.md:706:- Added depth-2 render-seed end-to-end test coverage (frac-0106): `tests/test_render_seed.py` now includes `RenderSeedEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `src/cypherclaw/render/seed.py` public surface through one realistic deterministic-seed lifecycle. The coverage walks a phrase → voice → event family of `seed_path` tuples through `derive_seed(...)` and asserts each sub-seed is in the 32-bit range, deterministic on re-derivation, and unique across the family; re-deriving the same family from a perturbed root seed produces a different sub-seed at every position; the same paths attached to `Event(seed_path=...)` instances preserve the tuple-cast invariant and re-derive to the original sub-seed via `event.seed_path`; and a JSON-safe `{root_seed, alt_root_seed, family: [{event_id, path, seed, alt_seed, event_seed_path}]}` diagnostic round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)` while preserving sub-seed values, event count, and per-position seeds. `tests/test_test_render_seed_depth.py` pins the render-seed test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the seed helper already produced meaningful one-path SHA-256 output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4637 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
